parameters:
Bard: And with this, Clea and the others' story comes to an
end.

Bard: Thank you for accompanying me with my tone-deaf
singing.

Girl Mel: So, what happened to Clea? Did she become the
guild master at the Adventurer's Guild?

Bard: It's like talking about the frame while looking at a
magnificent masterpiece.
Girl Mel: I don't really understand, but will you tell me?

\CL 【Clea's Aftermath as an Adventurer】Continuing her
activities at the Adventurer's Guild, Futera. With her fame
and high abilities, she becomes the face of the Adventurer's
Guild.

\CL Celis wore the cloak entrusted to her and continued to
swing her greatsword to shatter unreasonable violence.

\CL For the sake of someone, and above all, for Clea's own
dream.

Bard: That's a lie, actually she retired due to an injury
and became a priest.

Bard: No, actually the ending was that she had a dispute
with the guild, joined a mercenary group, and traveled
throughout the empire!

Bard: Wait a minute... Did she keep failing the exams to
enter the Magic Academy...?

Bard: Haha, because Clea was a person with various facets,
it's common for bards to embellish the ending in a funny and
interesting way.

Bard: Some people think Clea led a happy life, while others
think she led an unfortunate life.
Bard: How do you feel about dragons and greatswords?

Girl Mel: I want to believe that Clea continued to be happy
as an adventurer!

Bard: That's fine, it's important to come to a satisfactory
answer.

Bard: There is a poet who said that this world is a stage
and we all have roles given to us.

Bard: There may be actors who are forced into roles they
don't want, but you know, humans have the power to seize the
roles they want to become.

Bard: That's the strength of humans. Even as times change,
they have the power to carve out their own lives...
Girl Mel: It's about Clea and the others!

Bard: You can become anything you want, whether it's an
adventurer, a cook, or even a tone-deaf bard.
Girl Mel: I still don't know what I want to become...

Bard: Don't worry, this stage is vast and endlessly high.
You will naturally come to want to play a role and become
something.

Bard: When you stumble and fall, I want you to remember Clea
and the song of dragons and great swords.
Bard: Because humans can become anything they want to be.
Bard: Well, it's about time you went home.
Girl Mel: Yeah, let me hear another song!

Bard: Ahaha, if you don't mind a tone-deaf bard and a long
song.
\CL \ms[3]Humans are free to fly around this stage\|\|\|\^

\CL \ms[3]Well, many people forget that they have beautiful
wings\|\|\|\^

\CL \ms[3]That's why, in truth, you are free from being
defined as \|\|\|\^

\ms[2] Bard: Well then... I hope I can meet wonderful
performers on this stage again. \|\|\|\^
\CL \ms[3]The song I sing is a song of someone\|\|\^
\CL \ms[3]The story of actors who lived desperately\|\|\^

Bard: And with this, Clea and the others' story comes to an
end.

Bard: Thank you for accompanying me with my tone-deaf
singing.
Girl Mel: Did Clea and the others lose...?

Bard: That's a difficult question. The wicked queen called
herself the queen and ruled the empire.

Bard: But that didn't last long either, as she was killed by
the dragon she created herself.

Bard: After losing their ruler, the empire falls into a
civil war. And afterwards, instead of a king, the senate
will govern the empire.

Bard: And there, they remembered the brave prince who fought
against the wicked queen, along with Clea and the others.
Girl Mel: So, did Clea and the others win?

Bard: Winning or losing is just a fleeting moment in the
long history.
Bard: There is something else that is truly important.

Bard: In this world, there is a poet who said that everyone
has a role given to them on the stage.

Bard: But I think, even if it seems impossible, if you still
stand up and face it...

Bard: Rather than the role given to you, you can choose the
role you desire.
Girl Mel: It's difficult and I don't understand...

Bard: Hahaha, sorry. It means that anyone can become
[someone] if they wish.

Bard: I hope you also have an interesting life. When that
time comes, I apologize for being tone-deaf, but let me sing
your song.

Bard: It's already getting dark. It's about time you should
go home.
Girl Mel: Yes, please let me hear your song again!

Girl Mel: You know, it feels like you're talking about your
friends when you talk about Clea and the others!

Bard: I think they're a little different from friends, but
they were interesting people, so I had a lot to talk about
with them.
Girl Mel: You've talked to Clea before!?

Bard: I make sure to remember interesting people, so I
remember many people surrounding Clea.
Girl Mel: Please let me hear the rest someday!
Mel's Father: I was worried about you until this late.

Girl Mel: I was listening to the minstrel's song! It's a
story about a protagonist named Clea who is a dragon and
wields a great sword!

Mel's Father: You really do love stories, don't you? Anyway,
dragons and great swords... I've never heard of that before.
Girl Mel: Um, the Fotizona Empire is the setting!
Girl Mel: The minstrel actually met Clea!

Mel's Father: Ahahaha, you've been fooled! The Fotizona
Empire was a country that perished 500 years ago, you know?

Mel's Father: The only thing that remains is the old tavern
you often go to. I heard that Old Truvos was built during
the imperial era.
Mel's Father: That minstrel is just a big liar...
Mel's Father: Maybe he's lived a really long time.

Minstrel: Clea, I wonder... were you able to choose the role
you wanted to become?
Minstrel: Or perhaps, it was a role you didn't wish for?

Minstrel: I don't know about that, but I will deliver your
song to as many people as possible, even if I'm alone.

Minstrel: So that everyone can remember the dragon and the
great sword.
